We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

instruct the LDRRMO to (i) revise the MDRRFIP and MDRRMP to include in a separate caption the programs, projects and activities to be undertaken out of the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years and submit corresponding Accomplishment Report thereof; 
(ii) determine calamity-related PPAs and categorize them as to the four thematic areas pursuant to the DILG Policy; and 


(iii) apply for fidelity bond as the accountable officer for government-owned DRRM property;

direct the Municipal Accountant to include in the monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF those programs, projects and activities undertaken out of the unexpended balance from previous year in a separate caption for proper validation against the MDRRM Plan;

create and fill up the two positions approved under SB Resolution No. 18-019 so that the DRRMO can function efficiently and effectively; and

safeguard all procured and donated supplies, materials, equipment and relief goods against losses and wastages by providing adequate facility or warehouse.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive adopt the following courses of action; viz:

continue to exercise strong political will to implement the environmental laws on preserving and protecting the environment as mandated under Republic Act No. 9003 and existing Municipal Ordinances;

through Liga ng mga Barangay, encourage the active participation of barangay officials to support the solid waste management program of the Municipality by enforcing segregation of waste at source and “No segregation, No collection Policy” within the locality;

enforce strictly the sanctions against violators of the rules and regulations on ecological solid waste management in accordance with Sections 49 and 50 of the Act;

instruct the SWM Officer to expedite the repair of electrical wiring and make MRCF fully operational;




prioritize at all times the use of general mode of procurement and resort only to alternative modes if permitted by the circumstances laid down in the RIRR of R.A No. 9184; and

consider the safety and protection of garbage collectors by providing them with necessary wearable personal protective equipment.

